name: InstallationComplete
desc:
This state inidates installation is completed, this is a temporary state
as once this state is reached the LauncherStatusCubit.getStatus is called
and thus the completion status from that Launcher status will be used primarily

name: close
desc:
Closes the instance.
This method should be called when the instance is no longer needed.
Once close is called, the instance can no longer be used.

name: loadInstallationStatus
desc: This method connects to the websocket for getting the installation status

name: startInstallation
desc: Starts the installation

name: stopInstallation
desc: Stops the installation

name: InstallationError
desc:
Indicates the error happened during the installation, this indicates
installation is started but ended before completing the installation,
This state is used to indicate even when the websocket connection to
fetch installation status got any errors

name: Installing
desc: This state indicates installation is in progress

name: NotStarted
desc:
This is the state when InstallationCubit is initialised
and until the installation has started

name: StartingInstallation
desc: This state indicates InstallationCubit.startInstallation is being invoked

name: StopingInstallation
desc: This state indicates InstallationCubit.stopInstallation is being invoked

name: GetLauncherLoadedState
desc:
This extension on BuildContext is used to get the launcherStatus throughout
the application scope, it is casted directly as LauncherStatusLoaded because
only when the sstatus is LauncherStatusLoaded the application is rendered or else
Splash Screen in show during LauncherStatusLoading and an error is shown
when the state is LauncherStatusLoadingError on both these states this extension is of no use
